&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit e5b137d4b2ec9371a6f8a0a7fca3849730127302&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Zoran Regvart &amp;lt;zregvart@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2017-04-27T12:40:18Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11212&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t allow Salesforce HTTP client to stop with outstanding requests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-11212&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-11212&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Don&apos;t allow Salesforce HTTP client ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ...to stop with outstanding requests&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This introduces a `Phaser` to await for any in-flight requests to&lt;br/&gt;
    complete before the client is allowed to stop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This should not block as long as the&lt;br/&gt;
    `BufferingResponseListener::onComplete` is invoked at the end of every&lt;br/&gt;
    request. And that is guaranteed by the `CompleteListener::onComplete`&lt;br/&gt;
    contract.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
